<TEXT>
after an 11year hiatus pianist van cliburn 
resumed his public performances monday night to thunderous applause 
with a concert dedicated to two late friends 
the audience called the pianist back to the stage 13 times after 
he completed his program of liszts piano concerto no 1 and 
tchaikovskys piano concerto no 1 cliburn ended the evening with 
four encores 
this is a very sentimental evening for me clibuurn told the 
audience before the performance this is an evening of remembrance 
of two wonderful friends 
the pianist dedicated the concert at the openair mann music 
center to eugene ormandy and fredric r mann 
ormandy who died in 1985 was music director of the philadelphia 
orchestra for 44 years mann a former us ambassador headed the 
summer concert festival at the music center from 1949 until his 
death in 1987 
cliburn played with ormandy and the philadelphia musicians within 
weeks of gaining world fame for winning the first tchaikovsky 
international competition in 1958 the relationship yielded numerous 
concerts and recordings 
he also played in philadelphia in 1978 the year he quit 
performed publicly weary from a schedule that included 100 concerts 
a year 
he said he chose the liszt to honor ormandys hungarian 
background the program concluded with tchaikovskys piano concerto 
no 1 
cliburn spent the morning practicing with the orchestra and the 
afternoon shopping in philadelphia 
its so good to be back with the philadelphia orchestra it 
seems like i never left cliburn said after the practice session 
among his favorite venues cliburn always listed manns theater 
in fairmont park where he would often play to the audience long 
after the orchestra musicians had left for the night 
proceeds from monday nights concert will help finance the 
orchestras free summer series which ormandy and mann began 
roland condon of princess anne md who traveled with cliburn 
for six months two decades ago for a film project said the years 
dropped away from the pianist in profile 
you would never know it has been 11 years since he appeared 
before an audience like this condon said 
since 1978 he had performed in public only twice in december 
1987 and in january 1988 for private gatherings honoring 
respectively soviet leader mikhail gorbachev and the bob hope 
cultural center 
</TEXT>
