<TEXT>
summer is coming to central idahos camas 
prairie and harold stroud once again has his eye on soldier 
mountains last patch of snow and on his friends bill stewart and 
wes fields 
as they have for more than a decade the three have placed bets 
on when the final remnant of winter will disappear with dinner for 
the winner at stake its a bet that nature has not always been 
allowed to settle 
stroud is betting again that the snow will still being visible on 
aug 10 but he knows a lot can happen by then 
faced with losing several years ago when the snow was nearly gone 
