pollution cleanup promised by the steelmaker in 1987 
officials said that the agreement the largest ever negotiated by 
the state with an industrial polluter is legally binding and that 
bethlehem could be fined more than 100000 for failing to maintain 
the cleanup schedule 
bethlehem steels sparrows point complex at baltimore harbor 
employs 8000 workers and produces steel for ships bridges 
buildings autos and appliances 
