<TEXT>
wednesday is the summer solstice the longest 
day of the year in the northern hemisphere 
the solstice occurs at 553 am edt according to astronomers at 
the us naval observatory here the moment marks the time during 
the summer when the sun is farthest from the equator 
the date known in folklore as midsummer had been a time for 
parties and frivolity to celebrate the season 
listing the date as the start of summer has become a popular 
convention among calendar makers in recent years but the 
designation carries no official weight meteorologists for example 
consider summer to have begun june 1 
