safety problems because of the alleged illegal substitution of scrap 
metal for designated alloys in engines for 5000 military aircraft 
the pentagon said tuesday 
according to a fraud indictment monday in tampa fla of three 
former executives of aerodyne investment casings inc the company 
used scrap in making turbine blades of the type used in 22000 jet 
aircraft helicopters and tanks 
now its estimated that 5000 aircraft have been equipped with 
these parts since 1982 said pentagon spokesman pete williams 
two million hours have been accrued on the aircraft without any 
known related incidents 
there has been no noticeable degradation in performance using 
that 50percent mixture 
the blades were used in t53 engine thats used on the huey 
cobra and mohawk helicopters for the army he said 
