child and sometime lover as a young adult 
but there are two major problems with the film 
the first is that fosters character katy chandler never really 
gets a chance to develop we see far too little of her in the movie 
to really understand her motivation and direction or to explain her 
suicide 
the other problem is the overwhelming use of flashbacks the 
whole thing is a flashback with flashbacks inside the flashback 
which really jumbles the timing 
the story unwinds through harmon who daydreams as he sits on a 
minor league bench harmon as billy the charming allamerican kid 
does a neat job of coming back from a neerdowell to cleancut 
baseball player after he returns home to dispose of katys ashes 
