the federal reserve board has given final 
permission to a subsidiary of jp morgan amp co to underwrite 
corporate debt the first time the agency has granted that power to 
a commercial bank 
in january the federal reserve authorized jp morgan and four 
other large banks to expand their securities underwriting but 
withheld final approval until it could review the management and 
financing of the banks securities subsidiaries 
