government securities and to underwrite and deal in general 
obligation municipal bonds in january the fed ruled that banks 
could also underwrite corporate debt provided that the activity did 
not generate more than 5 percent of all securities income 
corporate debt underwriting within that limit will not violate 
the depressionera glasssteagall act which separated commercial 
from investment banking the fed ruled 
the agency is expected to decide early next year whether banks 
can engage in limited underwriting of corporate stock 
