here is a chronology of events in the takeover battle for nwa 
inc parent of northwest airlines 
march 28 after months of takeover rumors nwa chairman steven 
rothmeier announces that an unnamed investment group has accumulated 
49 percent of the companys stock and approached nwa about a 
possible acquisition rothmeier later identifies the suitor as a 
friendly group led by alfred checchi of los angeles 
march 30 oil billionaire marvin davis offers 267 billion or 
90 a share to buy nwa 
april 20 davis launches hostile 70 a share tender offer after 
the nwa board rejects his buyout proposal the board later advises 
shareholders not to sell to davis 
may 9 pan am corp chairman thomas plaskett announces his 
companys interest in acquiring northwest 
may 15 nwa holds its annual meeting in relative quiet after 
davis drops his threatened proxy fight to gain control of the board 
of directors in order to join the formal bidding process outlined by 
nwas board 
may 30 davis checchi pan am the international association of 
machinists and mei diversified inc run by minneapolis banker carl 
pohlad meet nwas first deadline for bids 
june 6 nwa rejects all bids but invites revisions 
june 16 davis checchi pan am and machinists union confirm 
theyve met the deadline for revised bids sources also say new york 
investment firm kohlberg kravis roberts amp co submits a proposal 
mei drops out 
june 18 checchis group meets in new york with nwa 
june 19 nwa and checchi sign a deal at 1 am edt under which 
his group would buy the airline for 121 a share or about 4 
billion 
