the dollar fell sharply against the japaense yen 
today while the tokyo stock exchanges key index rebounded 
the 225issue nikkei stock average gained 22029 points or 067 
percent finishing at 3323347 
the dollar closed at 14380 yen down 170 yen from mondays 
14550yen finish it opened at 14375 yen and moved between 14325 
yen and 14400 yen 
traders said most investors were adjusting their dollar holdings 
mainly because of uncertainties over the direction of the dollaryen 
rate after large swings last week 
the dollar closed thursday at 15130 yen its highest in almost 
two years and then fell 625 yen the next day 
yoshitsugu hanada a mitsui bank trader said investors were 
buying dollars at the 143yen level while japanese trading houses 
were selling as the dollar approached 144 yen 
in mixed trading the dollar has been gradually falling 
hamada said adding that most investors no longer are looking for an 
abrupt rise against the yen but this does not mean bullishness 
about the dollar has been totally reversed he said 
now is the adjustment phase after the dollars rapid rise to 
the 151yen level last week said hamada 
the bank of japan reportedly was selling dollars to support the 
yen but the amount was not known the central bank does not comment 
on its foreign exchange activities 
on the stock exchange dealers said the yens surge against the 
dollar reassured japanese investors encouraging stock purchases 
nomura securities analyst masahiro umemori said the market 
rebounded by itself mainly because of recent stability in foreign 
exchange 
its too early to say the strong yen is back but the foreign 
exchanges stability was at least good news for stock trading he 
said noting that the index had fallen more than 1100 points last 
week because of the dollars sharp rise against the yen 
trading however was still inactive due to lingering 
uncertainties over currency movements umemori said 
volume on the first section was estimated at 700 million shares 
up from 450 million the previous day 
among gainers were electricals including sony and sharp as well 
as steel and shipbuilding issuees 
