<TEXT>
sabena airlines said tuesday klm royal 
dutch airlines and british airways will invest in a new subsidiary 
to expand the belgian carrier and arm it against stiffer competition 
in a more deregulated european air traffic market in the 1990s 
sabena chairman carlos van rafelghem said sabena will have a 60 
percent stake in the new subsidiary called sabena world airlines 
with klm and british airways each owning 20 percent 
the new subsidiary must consolidate sabenas market share and 
help it turn the brussels airport sabenas home base into a 
european hub he said 
van rafelghem said sabena klm and british airways will remain 
independent carriers but he did not exclude further cooperation in 
air services in and out of brussels if such an arrangement is 
entirely compatible with eec competition law 
johan dekker sabenas vice president of operations said the 
participation of the dutch and british air carriers in the new 
subsidiary will run into billions of francs 
he declined to be more specific a billion francs is about 25 
million 
last year sabena increased its fleet and number of flights 
especially in europe began a 10 million expansion program on air 
and ground services throughout europe and also expanded services to 
the far east 
dekker said the injection of dutch and british capital into the 
new subsidiary will allow sabena to implement a quick expansion 
program to face stiffer competition as the european economic 
community moves to dismantle the communitys internal borders as of 
dec 31 1992 
</TEXT>
