<DOCNO> AP890620-0241 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
after 18 months of delays lotus development corp 
said today it has begun shipping its release 3 an improved version 
of the bestselling 123 computer software 
jim p manzi the companys 37yearold chairman made the 
announcement at lotus annual meeting in boston 
with the embarrassing delays last year lotus and release 3 had 
become the moral equivalent of the boston red sox in the world 
series manzi said 
we have come through a very tough period and i believe we have 
proved our mettle he said 
a key feature of the new software is the ability to display data 
in three dimensions 
other computer spreadsheets show information along two axes 
allowing for example a store manager who wants to analyze his 
seasonal sales pattern to put products along one axis and time 
periods along the other 
if he has several stores however the manager faces an 
additional headache with release 3 he can cure it by creating a 
third axis representing various stores or geographic regions 
after three years and tens of millions of dollars in development 
costs lotus is betting that 3d software unlike movies will turn 
out to be more than a quick fad not everyone is sure 
i think three dimensionality is a desirable function for a 
certain percentage of the market but what percentage i dont 
know said richard sherlund an analyst for goldman sachs amp co 
in new york not everyone needs it 
lotus founded in 1982 has grown from a handful of employees to 
more than 2600 worldwide on the strength of 123 its original 
product and still the source of nearly twothirds of its sales 
which are projected at more than 500 million this year 
but to keep ahead of competitors like microsoft corp of redmond 
wash and borland international corp of scotts valley calif 
lotus has had to continually upgrade the programs features 
for the topsecret release 3 project which lotus code named 
godiva the firm three years ago assembled a small team of 
engineers that quickly grew to more than 100 people a confident 
manzi announced in april 1987 that release 3 would be out in early 
1988 
but design and management problems about which the company has 
said little intervened 
lotus said in february 1988 that release 3 would not be ready 
until late in the second quarter of 1988 a month later the target 
date was pushed back to the fourth quarter then last october the 
company announced a further delay until the second quarter of 1989 
with its repeated failure to meet its own deadlines lotus 
earnings and stock price plunged and its competitors picked up 
market share 
manzi a former management consultant who had taken over from 
lotus founder mitch kapor in 1986 was stung by intensely personal 
negative publicity charles digate the executive in charge of 
spreadsheets resigned 
industry wags said the company was pioneering a new class of 
products called vaporware software that disappears every time 
it is about to be introduced 
but lotus apparently turned the corner last year when it brought 
in w frank king a former ibm manager to head up the project he 
injected discipline into the project team and got release 3 into 
field test in february 
as a result lotus stock has largely recovered trading recently 
at around 26 a share close to its 52week high of 2675 and far 
above its low for the year of 1475 
competitors are still close on the firms heels with microsoft 
steadily enhancing its excel software the no 2 spreadsheet on the 
market and borland reportedly working on a 3d version of its 
quattro program 
at lotus annual meeting today in the berklee performance center 
attended by more than 400 people the company showed a widescreen 
television transmission from its manufacturing center in cambridge 
with boxes of release 3 rolling off an assembly line and being 
packed for shipment to customers across the country 
the delays have cost them a lot of clout in the market and 
tarnished their reputation sherlund said in advance of the 
announcement now its their time to shine 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

