they filed a countersuit alleging slander and libel and claimed that 
hsn executives engaged in a blame the telephone company scheme to 
mask hsns poor market and financial performance 
gte counsel roy reardon told the jury that hsns charges were 
absolutely baseless 
hsn had 4 million subscribers when it talked to gte about 
telephone service in 1985 reardon said that grew to 9 million by 
august 1986 and one year later the number skyrocketed to 465 
million he said 
sales soared from 11 million in 1985 to 582 million by august 
1987 all with the gte telephone network in place he said 
we dont believe you just cover your own problems of 
mismanagement by blaming other people there was no fraud no 
coverup reardon said 
hsns original 12count complaint has been reduced to four 
charges fraud negligent misrepresentation breach of trust and 
confidence and breach of fiduciary duty 
pinellas circuit judge howard rives combined both suits in what 
is expected to be a sixweek trial 
although there are no phone company records showing the precise 
number of calls in question home shopping expects to show evidence 
that 42 million calls were not completed betweeen february 1986 and 
april 1987 kamin said 
he added that not all lost calls would have translated into sales 
kamin presented what he said was an internal gte memo that noted 
as many as 26000 overflow calls in a onehour period 
the inhouse document asks what are gte subsidiaries 
responsibilities to the customer and the efficiency of his service 
and notes that hsn is not aware that its calls are restricted 
it was in a sense a disaster waiting to happen kamin told 
the sixmember jury and five alternates 
after april 1987 surveys showed hsn was losing 50 percent of its 
calls the company switched carriers to mci communications corp 
kamin said adding the call completion rate now is over 90 percent 
</TEXT>
